node.text: Let’s hope it’s not harmful to them when the tourists come flocking back in
It's a start of back-to-nature. Dolphins and Dugongs are returning back to their waters, while humans are "Caved" in their homes 😂😂😂

WATCH: Aerial footage of a herd of more than 30 dugongs drifting serenely off the coast of southern Libong island in Thailand.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Thailand's tourism industry has taken a battering after the pandemic paralysed global travel, ⁣⁣but the slowdown in visitor foot traffic has brought a wildlife revival along shorelines and waterways. Video: AFP⁣⁣
⁣⁣
#linkinbio to read more
It will soon be over, like a diet, you eat less one day and compensate with vengeance the next days.
Time to appreciate the moment before the tourists come back
